oh bless us gedun drup a prayer hall for the dalai lama events at stanford oh bless us gedun drup a prayer hall for the dalai lama facebook twitter email print add to calendar khen rinpiche tsetan and sangye choedon co producers of the film the film shows the history of tashi lhunpo monastic university from the 15th century to the present and the relationship between the dalai lamas and panchen lamas who figure in the key events of that history the film also depicts some of the exile tibetan community's efforts to keep the dharma teachings alive the co producers of the film khen rinpoche tsetan and sangye choedon will introduce the film and take questions after the showing of the film co sponsored by the tibetan studies initiative and the stanford humanities center when thursday march 22 2012 7 30 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where levinthal hall stanford humanities center map audience general public faculty staff students alumni friends members tags lecture reading sponsor humanities center ho center for buddhist studies at stanford contact 650 736 1301 ihl stanford edu admission free and open to the public permalink http events stanford edu events 301 30159 more info last modified february 13 2012
